## What Is The Difference Between A Bachelors Degree And An Associates Degree In Nursing?

The difference between a bachelor's degree and associate degrees nursing lies within the scope of education. Bachelor's programs require four years of study while associates' courses last two years.

Bachelor's programs provide more comprehensive training than those offered through associate degrees. They also allow students to specialize in certain areas such as pediatrics, gerontology, etc., whereas most associate-level classes focus solely upon general health care knowledge.

## 1. Is mixed martial arts totally original from roman colosseum games?

MMA has been around since ancient times when gladiators fought each other.

The Romans had a sport called "gladiatoria" where they would pit animals against one another (usually lions) but also humans who could fight well enough to survive being eaten alive by these beasts. This was done so that spectators at the arena might see something more exciting than just watching men kill themselves over some trivial matter such as politics or religion; after all, what good is having money if you don't get any enjoyment out of life either way right now huh? So anyway...the point here is that while modern day mma may not look like much compared to its predecessors because we've got better technology nowadays which allows us to film everything going down inside those arenas back then - still though! It's pretty clear how closely related our current version actually IS TO THE OLDER FORMS OF FIGHTING SPORTS THAT WERE PRACTICED BY OUR ANCESTORS LONG AGO!

## 1. Is Mixed martial arts totally original from Roman Colosseum games?

MMA has been around since ancient times.

The Romans had gladiatorial contests where two men would fight each other until only one was left standing.
These fights often ended up being very bloody as both sides wanted to win so badly that they didn't care about hurting themselves too much either way (which led to many deaths).
This type of fighting also inspired modern day boxing which uses gloves instead of bare hands but still involves punching and kicking your opponent while trying not to get hit yourself!

In addition to these types of events there were also chariot races where teams raced against each other using horses pulling carts filled with weapons like swords etc... This event lasted longer than just watching someone die slowly over time because everyone involved knew what could happen if things went wrong - injuries might occur even though nobody wants those kinds of outcomes happening during competition!
